\[updated\]The FENKART (\"erkart\") Stack

\

\#erkartStack

\#pantheon

\

The purpose of this document is to outline the capabilities of the
next-gen, machine-learning-native enterprise architecture, with kind
rememberance named the Erkart Stack (Erdos-Kalman-Riemann-Turing).

\

\

Components:

-   Erdos.ai / SalienDB.ai (representational hyper-graph; data store)

-   Kalman.ai / Thalamus.ai (time-&energy-aware,
    representation-/value-aware proxy and/or trust/connectivity broken,
    with inspection callback for trusted parties; this is a smart router
    which is a point-of-embodiment (PoE) for partially-ordered
    chains/stacks of objective functions selection and executive
    manifestation of free-will )

-   Turing.ai / Lambda.ai (bounded-context computable functions, i.e.
    lambdas, reverse lambdas) - includes

-   Riemann.ai / Manifold.ai (computes/anneals and journals (stores)
    estimators of constrained latent manifold/space/field isomorphisms
    or lossy-isomorphisms; triple loss convolutional neural networks are
    a particular case; variational auto-encoders and GANs are the
    converse/reverse particular case)
